answers.body_markdown:
The &quot;Index 0 out of bounds for length 0&quot; error you&#39;re encountering is probably because of `input.nextLine()` call after reading an integer input using `input.nextInt()`. When you press Enter after entering the integer, the `input.nextLine()` reads the newline character (&#39;\n&#39;), which your code didn&#39;t capture.

To fix this, you can add an extra `input.nextLine()` after reading the integer to consume the newline character. Modify your code like this:

```java
choice = input.nextInt();
input.nextLine();
System.out.println();
if (choice == 1) {
    // ...
}
```

This should prevent the error now. Don&#39;t worry, I used to make this mistake all the time.

