IMO, Hibernate&#39;s behaviour looks more natural rather than your desire, at least it is consistent with the output `OffsetDateTime.now()`.

However, in any case you need to write some code to support desired behaviour, for example:

```java
// OffsetDateTimeUTCJavaDescriptor.java

public class OffsetDateTimeUTCJavaDescriptor extends OffsetDateTimeJavaDescriptor {

    public static final OffsetDateTimeUTCJavaDescriptor INSTANCE = new OffsetDateTimeUTCJavaDescriptor();

    @Override
    public &lt;X&gt; OffsetDateTime wrap(X value, WrapperOptions options) {
        OffsetDateTime result = super.wrap(value, options);
        if (result == null) {
            return null;
        }
        return result.withOffsetSameInstant(ZoneOffset.UTC);
    }
    
}

// OffsetDateTimeUTCType.java

public class OffsetDateTimeUTCType extends OffsetDateTimeType {

    public OffsetDateTimeUTCType() {
        setJavaTypeDescriptor(OffsetDateTimeUTCJavaDescriptor.INSTANCE);
    }

    @Override
    public OffsetDateTime seed(SharedSessionContractImplementor session) {
        return super.seed(session).withOffsetSameInstant(ZoneOffset.UTC);
    }

    @Override
    public OffsetDateTime next(OffsetDateTime current, SharedSessionContractImplementor session) {
        return super.next(current, session).withOffsetSameInstant(ZoneOffset.UTC);
    }

}

```

Now, the problem is `Hibernate` (at least `v5`) does not provide any option to sync database metadata with JPA metadata, so you need to do that ~manually and actually two options exist:

I. completely override built-in definition of `OffsetDateTime` type, and use new convention everywhere:

```java
// package-info.java

@TypeDef(name = &quot;OffsetDateTimeUTC&quot;, typeClass = OffsetDateTimeUTCType.class, defaultForType = OffsetDateTime.class)
package com.tld;

import org.hibernate.annotations.TypeDef;
import com.tld.OffsetDateTimeUTCType;

import java.time.OffsetDateTime;
```

II. just register new type definition without overriding defaults:

```java
// package-info.java

@TypeDef(name = &quot;OffsetDateTimeUTC&quot;, typeClass = OffsetDateTimeUTCType.class)
package com.tld;

import org.hibernate.annotations.TypeDef;
import com.tld.OffsetDateTimeUTCType;

import java.time.OffsetDateTime;
```

and apply it to columns via:

```java
@Type(type = &quot;OffsetDateTimeUTC&quot;)
```

