It is clear from the error message that the ```bean of type &#39;org.modelmapper.ModelMapper&#39;``` is missing. So please add the following bean to your project and try again.


```
@Bean
public ModelMapper modelMapper() {
    return new ModelMapper();
}
```

**Note :** *Add this bean in class annotated with ```@Configuration```.*

Your ModelMapper class is not registered as spring bean, it is just a normal java class.
 In order to fix that, you need to create a `@Configuration` class that will define the bean if you&#39;d like to autowire it.

    @Configuration
    public class AppConfiguration {
        @Bean
        public ModelMapper modelMapper() {
            return new ModelMapper();
        }
    } 

Otherwise, you cannot use spring dependency injection and you would have to create the object yourself with `new ModelMapper();`

Another tip is to avoid annotating fields with `@Autowire`. Constructor level annotation is enough.

