Now, the problem is large number of concurrent requests can not be handled because of limited resources in the server.
assume that only 10 concurrent requests are allowed, when a request came, if 10 ongoing requests are there , then the expected behavior should be defined (weather it return an error or request is queued. if it is second way, then probably caller get read timeout exceptions).

based on the expected behavior, there are lot of different solution, even you can implement your own solution or existing solution. technically this is called &quot;rate limit&quot; . bucket4j is one implementation you can use.
this is a kind of your own simple soution you can implement (not perfect, you can make it perfect by learning and using inbuilt synchronizers we have in java concurrent package )
